    What does Bundesliga mean in German?
    Federal League
    Therefore, while the Bundesliga literally means "Federal League", a more logical translation would simply be "German League", more specifically a nationwide German league encompassing the entire "Bund" instead of its regions.

    What does "Bundesliga" mean? | World Football FAQ

    What is German second division called?
    The 2. Bundesliga (Zweite Bundesliga [tsvat bndslia], lit. '2nd Federal League') is the second division of professional football in Germany. It was implemented 11 years after the founding of the Fuball-Bundesliga as the new second division for professional football.

    Has Bayern ever been relegated?
    Bayern Munich have never been relegated from the Bundesliga since earning promotion into the division ahead of the 1965/66 season. However, the Bavarians were relegated from top tier regional football a decade earlier, dropping from the Oberliga Sd to the 2. Oberliga Sd.Oct 18, 2023

    Who owns German football clubs?
    Bundesliga, a club must either wholly- or majority-own its association football team. In case of majority ownership, the football team is operated as a separate company, of which 50% of the votes plus one vote must belong to the parent club, while the rest of votes belong to the investors.

    Description

    The Bundesliga, sometimes referred to as the Fuball-Bundesliga or 1. Bundesliga, is a professional association football league in Germany. At the top of the German football league system, the Bundesliga is Germany's primary football competition. Wikipedia
    Confederation: UEFA
    Domestic cup(s): DFB-Pokal; DFL-Supercup
    Founded: 24 August 1963; 60 years ago
    International cup(s): UEFA Champions League; UEFA Europa League; UEFA Europa Conference League
    Level on pyramid: 1
    Most appearances: Charly Krbel (602)
